10 AN ACT
11 RELATING TO THE PUBLIC PEACE, HEALTH, SAFETY AND WELFARE;
12 AMENDING AND ENACTING SECTIONS OF THE ELECTION CODE;
13 PROHIBITING PERSONS ACTING UNDER COLOR OF LAW OR OTHERWISE FROM
14 ORDERING TROOPS TO A PLACE WHERE AN ELECTION IS HELD UNLESS
15 NECESSARY TO REPEL ARMED ENEMIES OF THE UNITED STATES;
16 PROHIBITING INTERFERENCE WITH A PERSON'S RIGHT OF SUFFRAGE AT
17 AN ELECTION; PROVIDING PENALTIES; PROVIDING REMEDIES; PROVIDING
18 PROCEDURES FOR ELECTIONS FOLLOWING A DECLARATION OF A STATE OF
19 EMERGENCY.
20
21 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF NEW MEXICO:
22 SECTION 1. A new section of the Election Code, Section
23 1-1-29 NMSA 1978, is enacted to read:
24 "1-1-29. [NEW MATERIAL] UNDER COLOR OF LAW.--As used in
25 the Election Code, "under color of law" means acting or
